Athamantem: Athamas, father of Phrixus and Helle by Nephele, and of Learchus and Melicerta by Ino, was driven mad by Juno and slew Learchus and pursued Ino, who jumped into the sea with Melicerta, whereupon she was changed into Leucothea and M. into Palaemon. Cf. i 12, 28 n.; ovid, Met. iv 416—562.

Alcmaeonem: Amphiaraus joined the expedition of the Seven against Thebes, induced thereto by his wife Eriphyle, who had been bribed with the gift of the golden necklace. At Thebes the earth opened and swallowed him together with his chariot. Before quitting Argos, know- ing the fate that was in store for him, he charged his sons to avenge him upon their mother when they should be grown up. Alcmaeon accordinglyslewhisrnother and was in consequence driven mad and perseeuted by the Furies. Cf. ii 25, 60.
